Understood, I'm not convinced that the complexity added is worth the performance hit. A reorg is a rare occurence.

@sdaftuar,  your condition for reusing cached height is wrong. There is possibility that this returns false, but still need a refresh.
I think there is a simpler thing to do : Storing only the block hash of the youngest input in the mempool. If this block hash is still in the main chain during reorg, then no need to CheckSequenceLock for the entry. I'll try to do something along these lines by following your example.
